WEBVTT

00:04.266 --> 00:05.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.400 --> 00:07.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:07.366 --> 00:11.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:
The Washington Post reports
President Trump revealed highly

00:11.166 --> 00:16.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
classified material to Russia's
foreign minister and ambassador
during their visit to the Oval

00:17.100 --> 00:18.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Office.

00:18.366 --> 00:21.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Then: a hack felt
around the world.

00:21.333 --> 00:26.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We talk to the president of
Microsoft about the cyber-attack
leaving hospitals and businesses

00:27.533 --> 00:32.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
in 150 countries facing
ransom for their files.

00:34.400 --> 00:37.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And our Politics Monday duo
explore what the fallout from
the firing of the FBI director

00:39.133 --> 00:42.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
could mean for President
Trump's agenda going forward.

00:42.300 --> 00:47.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
All that and more on
tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

00:49.166 --> 00:52.000 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:52.000 --> 00:57.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: There's word
tonight that President Trump may
have jeopardized a secret source

01:01.900 --> 01:04.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of intelligence on the
Islamic State group.

01:04.933 --> 01:09.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Washington Post is reporting
that the president divulged
highly sensitive information

01:11.900 --> 01:14.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
when he met with the Russian
foreign minister and Russian
ambassador last week.

01:14.866 --> 01:19.866 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The account says an ally
provided the intelligence,
but had not given
permission to share it with

01:20.366 --> 01:22.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Russia.

01:22.366 --> 01:26.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're joined now by Greg Jaffe,
one of the Washington Post
reporters who broke the story.

01:26.133 --> 01:29.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Greg Jaffe, tell us exactly
what happened, as you know it.

01:29.633 --> 01:32.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GREG JAFFE, The Washington
Post: So, the meeting with the
Russian foreign minister and the

01:32.000 --> 01:34.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Russian ambassador
was taking place.

01:34.033 --> 01:38.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the president was sharing
information with them with
regard to the laptop threat

01:38.766 --> 01:43.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that had been an issue -- the
concern -- the threat posed
by laptops -- the threat posed

01:46.066 --> 01:48.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
by aviation to laptops,
which had been an issue.

01:48.333 --> 01:53.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he was describing the nature
of that threat, was boasting
about the great intel he had

01:54.800 --> 01:57.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and, in doing so, may have
overstepped the bounds.

01:57.433 --> 02:01.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, this is
information that had come from
a U.S. ally, is that correct?

02:01.966 --> 02:03.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
GREG JAFFE: Yes,
that's exactly right.

02:03.900 --> 02:08.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's particularly sensitive,
and I think the ally which
controls the dissemination

02:10.933 --> 02:14.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
of the information would be
upset to have learned that it
landed in the Russians' hands.

02:15.966 --> 02:18.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: It sounds as
if, from your reporting, Greg,
that the White House recognized

02:18.933 --> 02:23.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
pretty quickly what had
happened, because you wrote that
they contacted both the CIA

02:23.733 --> 02:26.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and the National Security
Agency afterwards.

02:26.100 --> 02:28.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
GREG JAFFE: Yes,
that's exactly right.

02:28.633 --> 02:33.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And they -- you know, they
controlled dissemination
of the transcripts
immediately afterwards.

02:35.200 --> 02:39.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they struck the references
to a sort of memo summary that
went out in the White House

02:41.400 --> 02:44.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
describing the meeting to
ensure that the information
didn't get out any further than

02:45.500 --> 02:47.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
it already had.

02:47.033 --> 02:48.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Obviously, the problem is not
internal to the U.S. government.

02:48.400 --> 02:50.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The problem is the
dissemination to the Russians.

02:50.833 --> 02:53.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What is the
damage done here potentially?

02:53.866 --> 02:56.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GREG JAFFE: You know, I think
there are a couple of concerns.

02:56.966 --> 03:01.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, you worry first and
foremost about potentially
compromising sources and methods

03:03.933 --> 03:07.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that allowed us -- that has
allowed us to gather this
intelligence over a period of

03:07.900 --> 03:09.833 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
time.

03:09.833 --> 03:12.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
My understanding is that
this is sort of a stream of
intelligence that's been useful

03:12.633 --> 03:16.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
over quite a period of
time, so I think that's the
first and foremost worry.

03:16.833 --> 03:20.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The secondary worry is that
you compromise a relationship
with an important ally.

03:20.566 --> 03:24.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: I'm going
to read back to you what
you quote in the story.

03:24.333 --> 03:29.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And you're quoting H.R.
McMaster, the president's
national security adviser.

03:31.333 --> 03:34.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He said to you that at no time
were any intelligence sources or
methods discussed, and he said

03:36.366 --> 03:40.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
no military operations were
not already disclosed that were
not already known publicly.

03:40.100 --> 03:42.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
GREG JAFFE: Yes, I
think that's right.

03:42.033 --> 03:46.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think the worry is, by giving
-- sharing this intelligence
with the Russians, that

03:48.000 --> 03:49.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
it potentially compromises
sources and methods.

03:49.933 --> 03:53.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In other words, this was
information that was shared
that the Russians weren't aware

03:53.133 --> 03:55.166 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
of.

03:55.166 --> 03:57.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They didn't know how we had
access to it, so I think the
worry is that you -- that their

03:57.700 --> 04:02.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ability is to reverse-engineer,
to sort of figure out where
this information was coming

04:03.633 --> 04:05.666 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
from.

04:05.666 --> 04:08.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Clearly, Greg
Jaffe, you're not going to tell
us your source on this story,

04:08.633 --> 04:12.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
but is it fair to say the
White House didn't want
this information revealed?

04:12.166 --> 04:16.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GREG JAFFE: Yes, I think that's
very fair to say that the
White House is very concerned,

04:16.466 --> 04:20.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think, both about the
information shared in the Oval
Office and about the story.

04:20.133 --> 04:22.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Where
does this go from here?

04:22.600 --> 04:27.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, the president has shared
this in a conversation
with the Russian foreign
minister, the Russian

04:27.033 --> 04:28.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ambassador to the U.S.

04:28.833 --> 04:31.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What can one expect?

04:31.433 --> 04:34.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Has there been an apology
made to the ally, the
country, the officials
from whom the information

04:37.133 --> 04:38.566 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
came?

04:38.566 --> 04:41.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
GREG JAFFE: You know, I don't
know the answer to that.

04:41.066 --> 04:45.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, I think this is one
of those issues where it's so
unprecedented, that I'm not

04:45.433 --> 04:47.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
sure where it goes from here.

04:47.400 --> 04:51.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I have been reporting on
national security matters for
quite a while, and it's hard to

04:52.766 --> 04:54.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
recall something like this.

04:54.900 --> 04:59.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Are presidents
given some sort of training or
guidance on how to talk about

05:00.900 --> 05:02.866 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
intelligence?

05:02.866 --> 05:04.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GREG JAFFE: Well, you know,
they get talking points
prior to the meetings.

05:04.966 --> 05:07.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And this is where it's important
to have talking points and have
a staff prepare the president

05:07.833 --> 05:10.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
and have the president
be willing to listen
and be prepared.

05:10.633 --> 05:15.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think that's the concern,
that this is a president who
doesn't have a long history

05:15.100 --> 05:20.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in government, is a president
who relies on his gut and
likes to wing it in meetings.

05:21.566 --> 05:24.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And I think that's
the concern here.

05:24.000 --> 05:29.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have to be open to being
staffed, and I think that's
potentially what was worrisome

05:30.033 --> 05:32.033 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
here.

05:32.033 --> 05:35.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Greg Jaffe of
The Washington Post, one of
the reporters on the story that

05:35.033 --> 05:37.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
has just broken within the
hour, Greg, we thank you.

05:37.400 --> 05:39.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
GREG JAFFE: Yes,
thanks for having me.

05:39.566 --> 05:44.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And in the
day's other news: The president
said the White House is moving

05:44.300 --> 05:49.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
rapidly to replace the man he
fired last week as director
of the FBI, James Comey.

05:50.766 --> 05:53.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
At least eight candidates were
interviewed over the weekend.

05:53.200 --> 05:57.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They included, among
others, acting FBI Director
Andrew McCabe, Republican
Senator John Cornyn

05:59.066 --> 06:03.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of Texas and a former Republican
congressman, Mike Rogers.

06:03.133 --> 06:08.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Meanwhile, the White House
press insisted today that the
president wants a full FBI

06:10.100 --> 06:12.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
review of Russian meddling
in the election, no
matter what it concludes.

06:12.133 --> 06:16.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SEAN SPICER, White House Press
Secretary: The actions that
he took, he knew could be

06:16.533 --> 06:21.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
detrimental to himself, but
none of those things mattered,
because the president had

06:21.100 --> 06:26.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to do the right thing for the
American people because he
believes that Jim Comey was the

06:26.100 --> 06:28.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
wrong man for that position.

06:28.066 --> 06:31.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: The president
himself has called the
investigation a charade.

06:31.833 --> 06:36.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Spicer also refused, again, to
confirm or deny that Mr. Trump
audiotaped his conversations

06:38.000 --> 06:40.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
with James Comey or
with anyone else.

06:40.900 --> 06:45.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Deputy Attorney General
Rod Rosenstein will brief
the full Senate on the
firing this Thursday.

06:47.766 --> 06:52.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The United Nations is nearly
doubling its appeal for
humanitarian aid in South Sudan,

06:53.100 --> 06:55.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
facing a brutal
civil war and famine.

06:55.766 --> 07:00.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The director of the World
Food Program warned today
that the suffering is --
quote -- "unimaginable."

07:02.000 --> 07:05.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
U.N. agencies said they need
at least $1.4 billion to
provide assistance to refugees.

07:07.833 --> 07:12.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The United States accused the
government of Syria today of
killing thousands of prisoners,

07:12.533 --> 07:15.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
and burning the bodies
to hide the evidence.

07:15.233 --> 07:20.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A top State Department official
said mass executions are
taking place about 45 minutes

07:21.433 --> 07:23.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
outside Damascus at a
large prison facility.

07:23.966 --> 07:25.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
STUART JONES, Acting
Assistant U.S. Secretary
for Near East Affairs:
The regime is responsible

07:25.533 --> 07:30.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for killing as many as 50
detainees per day at Sednaya.

07:32.566 --> 07:36.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Credible sources have believed
that many of the bodies have
been disposed in mass graves.

07:38.966 --> 07:42.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We now believe that
the Syrian regime has
installed a crematorium
in the Sednaya prison

07:44.466 --> 07:47.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
complex, which could
dispose of detainees remains
with little evidence.

07:47.866 --> 07:52.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: State Department
officials also called for
Russia to use its influence

07:52.133 --> 07:55.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
with the Damascus regime
to stop the atrocities.

07:55.400 --> 08:00.433 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The U.S. Supreme Court
will not hear an appeal to
reinstate North Carolina's
voter identification

08:02.866 --> 08:04.366 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
law.

08:04.366 --> 08:06.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Today's announcement leaves a
lower court ruling in place.

08:06.966 --> 08:11.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It found that the law
targeted African-Americans
with what it called --
quote -- "almost surgical

08:11.533 --> 08:13.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
precision."

08:13.600 --> 08:17.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The law imposed stricter I.D.
requirements, rolled back early
voting and eliminated same-day

08:19.200 --> 08:21.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
registration.

08:21.200 --> 08:25.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the second Monday in a row,
a federal appeals court has
heard arguments on President

08:25.933 --> 08:27.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Trump's travel ban.

08:27.900 --> 08:31.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This time, a panel of the Ninth
Circuit Court of Appeals, in
Seattle, heard a challenge

08:31.533 --> 08:33.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
by the state of Hawaii.

08:33.566 --> 08:38.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Judges pressed a top Justice
Department lawyer on whether the
ban on travel from six Muslim

08:39.900 --> 08:42.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
nations is, indeed,
religious discrimination.

08:42.433 --> 08:46.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDGE MICHAEL HAWKINS,
Ninth Circuit of Appeals:
Has the president ever
disavowed his campaign

08:46.600 --> 08:48.666 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
statements?

08:48.666 --> 08:53.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Has he ever stood up and said,
I said before I wanted to ban
all members of the Islamic

08:54.500 --> 08:57.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
faith from entering the United
States of America, I was wrong?

08:57.266 --> 09:02.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY WALL, Attorney:
Over time, the president
clarified that what he
was talking about were

09:02.033 --> 09:06.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Islamic terrorist groups,
and the countries that
shelter or sponsor them.

09:06.466 --> 09:10.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, over time, he and his
advisers clarified that what he
was focused on were groups like

09:10.800 --> 09:12.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
ISIS and al-Qaida.

09:12.866 --> 09:16.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Last
week, an appeals court
in Richmond, Virginia,
heard similar arguments

09:16.666 --> 09:19.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
in another suit
against the travel ban.

09:19.500 --> 09:21.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The Trump Cabinet
is now complete.

09:21.866 --> 09:26.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Robert Lighthizer was
sworn in today as U.S.
trade representative.

09:26.033 --> 09:29.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Vice President Mike Pence
presided over the ceremony.

09:29.133 --> 09:33.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Lighthizer is the last
Cabinet official to be
confirmed by the Senate.

09:33.133 --> 09:37.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He's expected to play a key role
in renegotiating trade deals.

09:37.866 --> 09:42.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And on Wall Street, stocks
rose, as oil prices surged.

09:42.566 --> 09:47.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The Dow Jones industrial
average gained 85 points
to close near 20982.

09:48.733 --> 09:51.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The Nasdaq rose 28, and
the S&amp;P 500 added 11.

09:51.666 --> 09:56.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Still to come on the "NewsHour":
the president of Microsoft on a
global cyber-attack; heightened

09:58.633 --> 10:03.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
threats from North
Korea's latest missile
launch; new limits by
the Trump administration

10:04.866 --> 10:09.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
on foreign aid to groups
that provide abortion
services; and much more.

10:16.233 --> 10:21.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The worldwide cyber-attack
appeared to slow today.

10:23.800 --> 10:28.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Since Friday, the so-called
ransomware has hit more than
200,000 victims in more than

10:29.566 --> 10:31.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
150 countries.

10:31.300 --> 10:34.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The worst of it
today was in Asia.

10:34.100 --> 10:36.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
