the group than any other.

30:47.800 --> 30:51.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Jeffrey Brown reports
on what kind of welcome
they will be receiving.

30:51.866 --> 30:56.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: A protest earlier
this year on the streets of
Tunis, a sign of democracy

30:58.966 --> 31:02.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the new Tunisia, where past
demonstrations would have been
brutally suppressed, but also

31:03.466 --> 31:06.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
a sign of lingering
political crisis.

31:06.666 --> 31:10.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Citizens rallied against the
return of thousands of fellow
Tunisians who have fought abroad

31:10.933 --> 31:15.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for the Islamic State and
other jihadi groups, and
now want to return home.

31:15.466 --> 31:16.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

31:16.933 --> 31:18.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
NAZIHA GOUIDER, Activist:
These people are not Tunisian.

31:18.900 --> 31:20.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They are monsters.

31:20.566 --> 31:23.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Dr.
Naziha Gouider helped
organize the protests.

31:23.833 --> 31:28.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She's a neurologist
in a well-off suburb
of Tunis and fears the
impact the returnees will

31:29.300 --> 31:29.833 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
have.

31:29.833 --> 31:31.233 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

31:31.233 --> 31:33.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
NAZIHA GOUIDER: They are
people who have no nationality.

31:33.733 --> 31:38.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They decided to go to a place
where -- to have another
nationality, because this place

31:40.000 --> 31:41.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is called a state.

31:41.000 --> 31:42.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: ISIS.

31:42.000 --> 31:43.000 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

31:43.000 --> 31:45.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
NAZIHA GOUIDER: Yes.

31:45.066 --> 31:47.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: But
family members of those
accused of fighting for
ISIS just want their

31:47.333 --> 31:49.766 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
loved ones home.

31:49.766 --> 31:53.066 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator):
My brother is one of
Tunisia's young people
who were marginalized,

31:53.066 --> 31:55.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
who got lost.

31:55.200 --> 31:59.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Before dawn on a
recent morning, this woman -- we
agreed to conceal her identity

32:01.766 --> 32:04.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
- - was on her way to a local
jail to visit her brother, a
young man, she said, who'd

32:06.200 --> 32:08.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
misled his family and left
to fight in Syria in 2012.

32:08.466 --> 32:12.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator): I
took him to the airport myself.

32:12.733 --> 32:14.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And that's what hurts me.

32:14.233 --> 32:18.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He contacted me and he told
me: "I'm in Syria and I'm OK."

32:18.733 --> 32:20.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You can imagine our situation.

32:20.800 --> 32:22.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We went mad.

32:22.333 --> 32:24.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I was crying while walking
in the street like a fool

32:24.466 --> 32:29.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Soon enough,
she says, her brother realized
he'd made a terrible mistake.

32:29.033 --> 32:32.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Eventually, he turned
himself into the Tunisian
Embassy in Turkey.

32:32.466 --> 32:36.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Returned to Tunis, he now faces
a lengthy prison sentence.

32:36.366 --> 32:40.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator): Now
he has the title of terrorist.

32:40.100 --> 32:41.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
His life is destroyed.

32:41.633 --> 32:43.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He is not the only one.

32:43.733 --> 32:48.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: The U.N.
estimates that between
5,000 to 6,000 Tunisians
joined ISIS to fight

32:49.766 --> 32:53.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in Syria, Iraq, and Libya, more
than from any other country.

32:53.800 --> 32:57.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The response to the returning
fighters is a complicated
one, in a country with a very

32:57.966 --> 33:02.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
fragile democracy and very
real security concerns.

33:05.333 --> 33:08.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Protests in 2011 in Tunisia
peacefully overthrew
longtime dictator Abidine
Ben Ali and sparked

33:10.366 --> 33:12.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the wider Arab Spring uprisings.

33:12.833 --> 33:17.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Later, a democratically elected
coalition government included
Tunisian secularists and

33:18.733 --> 33:20.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Islamists.

33:20.833 --> 33:25.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is a country widely seen as
the region's success story, but
one with enormous challenges,

33:27.566 --> 33:30.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
including a stagnant
economy and large numbers
of homegrown terrorists.

33:30.933 --> 33:35.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In 2015, 20 tourists were
killed by Islamist gunmen at
Tunis' Bardo Museum, a cultural

33:38.366 --> 33:40.400 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
treasure.

33:40.400 --> 33:44.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And a lone gunman killed
38, mostly Brits on holiday,
at a coastal beach resort.

33:45.666 --> 33:49.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
ISIS claimed responsibility
for both attacks.

33:49.033 --> 33:53.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Tunisian-born radicals have
also carried out attacks abroad,
including those in Nice and

33:53.633 --> 33:56.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Berlin in 2016.

33:56.033 --> 34:01.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Authorities here say about 800
Tunisian fighters have returned
and are now sitting in jails.

34:03.033 --> 34:05.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But hundreds more may have
snuck into the country
through neighboring Libya.

34:05.666 --> 34:07.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MOHAMED IQBAL, Rescue
Association of Tunisians
Trapped Abroad (through
translator): If you

34:07.766 --> 34:12.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ask any Tunisian family, do
you know of a Tunisian who
has gone to Syria or tried to

34:12.566 --> 34:15.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
go, they will say,
yes, of course we do.

34:15.233 --> 34:20.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Mohamed Iqbal
has spent the last several
years tracking those who left,

34:21.900 --> 34:24.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
and in 2013 formed
an organization to
help them return.

34:24.133 --> 34:25.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
A young boy.

34:25.600 --> 34:28.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MOHAMED IQBAL: Yes, a young
boy, about 16 years old.

34:28.400 --> 34:31.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: He was 16
when he went to Libya?

34:31.533 --> 34:34.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
MOHAMED IQBAL: Yes, 16
to Libya and to Syria.

34:34.466 --> 34:39.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Iqbal sees a
lost generation, many of them
poor and vulnerable Tunisians,

34:41.466 --> 34:45.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
succumbing to economic hardship
and a sophisticated network of
hard-line Islamists recruiting

34:46.500 --> 34:48.466 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
them for jihad.

34:48.466 --> 34:50.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MOHAMED IQBAL (through
translator): The lion knows
how to choose its prey.

34:50.700 --> 34:54.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There are recruitment networks
hunting for young people.

34:54.000 --> 34:59.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: The 2011
revolution unleashed
many disparate forces,
including an Islamist

35:01.933 --> 35:04.000 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
revival.

35:04.000 --> 35:08.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This video from that time shows
an imam who would later become
minister of religious affairs

35:08.100 --> 35:10.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
during Friday prayers.

35:10.166 --> 35:14.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN (through translator): It
is the duty of every Muslim
to help our brothers fight in

35:14.100 --> 35:16.166 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Syria.

35:16.166 --> 35:20.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Many accepted
that call, including Mohamed
Iqbal's younger brother.

35:21.866 --> 35:24.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We agreed not use his
name or show his face.

35:24.266 --> 35:27.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MAN (through translator): I
thought, by going, that I would
be helping to send a message

35:27.633 --> 35:32.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to the world: Enough
killings of the Syrian people
and the Muslim people.

35:32.000 --> 35:35.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have been told that,
in Syria, they will employ
us, provide us a house.

35:35.666 --> 35:38.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
If you want to get married,
you can do it there.

35:38.033 --> 35:42.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Despite being
wheelchair-bound, the younger
Iqbal managed to make it to the

35:42.333 --> 35:47.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Syrian border in 2013,
before his brother
convinced him to come home.

35:49.266 --> 35:52.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's now in a legal limbo
and regularly visited
and watched by police.

35:54.666 --> 35:57.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mohamed Iqbal acknowledges
that there are hardcore
terrorists among those who left.

35:57.600 --> 36:02.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He wants distinctions drawn
and efforts made to incorporate
as many as possible back into

36:03.066 --> 36:05.566 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
society.

36:05.566 --> 36:07.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MOHAMED IQBAL (through
translator): Tunisian
law can't prevent a
citizens from coming back

36:07.500 --> 36:09.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to his home country.

36:09.400 --> 36:13.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
These fighters must return
to their countries, get
arrested, and be rehabilitated.

36:13.100 --> 36:16.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
This is better than
they're remaining free
in areas of conflicts.

36:16.000 --> 36:20.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We want them to come back to
society and live normally,
not just as ex-convicts.

36:20.533 --> 36:25.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They must be producing
something to the society,
not only consuming.

36:25.100 --> 36:29.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: But to
what kind of society?

36:29.233 --> 36:33.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Tied up in Tunisia's
debates, the role of
religion in public life.

36:33.633 --> 36:38.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The former dictatorship
ruthlessly enforced secularism
and closely monitored religious

36:39.233 --> 36:40.900 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
activity.

36:40.900 --> 36:44.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
One result, people
like Imam Omar Mighri
spent years in prison.

36:44.200 --> 36:49.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, though, he is a moderate
who works with the government
to oppose radical Islamists

36:50.366 --> 36:52.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
whose influence grew
after the revolution.

36:52.366 --> 36:56.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At his home in a suburb of
Tunis, Imam Mighri told us that
forgiveness is one part of the

36:57.933 --> 37:01.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
equation, along with extensive
re-education programs.

37:01.233 --> 37:05.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
OMAR MIGHRI, Imam (through
translator): Many of them do
not have a proper understanding

37:05.333 --> 37:06.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of Islam and jihad.

37:06.833 --> 37:09.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They're a danger to society
and to our social fabric.

37:09.800 --> 37:14.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The government,
he says, must do more to reach
radicals in prisons and schools.

37:16.833 --> 37:19.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
OMAR MIGHRI (through
translator): We asked
the government to give
us the opportunity

37:19.433 --> 37:23.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
to speak to people who
have been jailed and try
to change their path.

37:23.333 --> 37:24.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We were refused.

37:24.600 --> 37:27.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Does the
government have a plan?

37:27.100 --> 37:32.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Yes, says Colonel Mohktar Ben
Nasr, a retired military officer
who now runs a think tank,

37:34.033 --> 37:37.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to jail the worst and
monitor others, through tight
security and the rule of law.

37:38.000 --> 37:40.333 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
COL.

37:40.333 --> 37:41.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MOHKTAR BEN NASR (RET.),
Former Tunisian Military
Official (through
translator): ISIS is a beaten

37:41.800 --> 37:44.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
force, so they will come back
in search of safe places.

37:44.300 --> 37:47.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The real difficulty lies
in identifying them,
because many don't return
through the airports

37:47.933 --> 37:50.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
with official documents.

37:50.533 --> 37:54.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Tunisia is
still a young democracy,
finding its way between
the security and these

37:57.333 --> 37:59.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
kinds of new freedoms.

37:59.166 --> 38:01.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Is it a difficult
balance even today?

38:01.533 --> 38:03.000 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
COL.

38:03.000 --> 38:05.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MOHKTAR BEN NASR (through
translator): Yes, absolutely.

38:05.033 --> 38:08.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, the guaranteed thing
is that there is real freedom,
there is freedom of expression.

38:08.700 --> 38:10.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But this freedom has limits.

38:10.200 --> 38:13.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And when people overstep
those limits, there is chaos.

38:13.000 --> 38:18.000 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: After
human rights groups issued
reports on abuses by
Tunisian security forces,

38:19.933 --> 38:23.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
civil liberties advocates
responded with a campaign called
No to Terrorism, Yes to Human

38:25.000 --> 38:27.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Rights, featuring prominent
Tunisian celebrities.

38:27.933 --> 38:31.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
